A LIST OF THE 1000 MOST POPULAR “CAN” QUESTIONS ON GOOGLE

One of the most widely used modal verbs in English, “Can” is used to express ability or opportunity, to show possibility or impossibility and to request or offer permission.

The reason why we have included a bit about the usage of the word “Can” is to show the variety of ways in which this verb can be used. However, when it comes to searches around the globe, there are thousands of people searching variety of questions starting with the word “Can”. And no wonder, PPC experts, advertisers and marketers are paying quite a few dollars for these terms.

So, in here, we have included the entire list of top 1000 most frequently asked “Can” questions on Google. Alongside you will also find the global search volume and cost-per-click (CPC) data. CPC or cost-per-click refers to the amount advertisers pay to advertise for that term on Google.

WHAT ARE THE MOST POPULAR “Can” QUESTIONS IN THE WORLD?

Taking a quick look at the results, we were able to see that the top rank belongs to the term – “Can you ran it” with approx 550,000 searches. Coming a distant second is the term/question – “Can I run it” with 368,000 searches. The third spot belongs to the question – “Can you feel the love tonight” with 90,500 worldwide searches.

Like this, there are many more shocking phrases or rather questions that show up in this list of the most asked “Can” questions on Google.

Meanwhile, in this list of most asked 1000 “Can” questions on Google, we have not tried to exclude TV shows, web series, popular chart buster songs as well as movies as we believe these are genuine “Can” questions asked on Google.

This makes this list of most asked “Can” questions way too fascinating for marketers out there.
